Idea
Tax Filing Simulation & Training Platform

(GST, ITR & Tax Return Practice Portal)

1. Executive Summary

We are building a digital tax filing simulation platform that trains students, professionals, and aspiring accountants on how to file taxes in India.

The platform recreates the complete workflow of tax filing—including GST returns, income tax returns, and compliance tasks—in a safe, simulated environment where users can practice without interacting with real government systems.

Students will learn the exact process followed on official platforms like:

GST Portal (India)

Income Tax e-Filing Portal (India)

However, the system will be fully independent and educational, using dummy data and training scenarios.

Our goal is to become the primary training platform for tax education in India.

2. Problem Statement

Tax compliance in India is complex and constantly evolving.

Current challenges

Students learn theory but not practical filing

Training institutes rely on screenshots or outdated demos

Practicing on live government portals is not possible or safe

New accountants often make mistakes due to lack of hands-on experience

This creates a major skill gap between education and professional practice.

3. Solution

We propose a Tax Filing Simulation Platform that allows learners to:

Practice filing GST returns

Simulate Income Tax Return (ITR) submissions

Perform tax calculations

Upload invoices

Generate returns and acknowledgments

The platform replicates the complete workflow of real tax filing systems, providing students with hands-on training before entering the workforce.

4. Product Overview

The platform will include three major simulation modules.

Module 1: GST Filing Simulation

Students will learn the entire GST workflow.

Features:

Business registration simulation

GSTIN generation (dummy)

Invoice entry system

Sales and purchase registers

Return generation

Simulated forms:

GSTR-1

GSTR-3B

Tax liability summary

Filing confirmation

Learning outcome:
Students understand monthly GST compliance processes.

Module 2: Income Tax Return (ITR) Filing Simulation

This module teaches individuals how to file personal income tax returns.

Students will learn:

Income declaration

Salary entry

Capital gains entry

Business income entry

Deduction calculations

Examples of deductions:

Section 80C

Section 80D

Housing loan interest

The system calculates tax based on the latest Indian tax slabs and generates simulated ITR forms.

Module 3: Tax Compliance Dashboard

A dashboard where users can monitor tax obligations.

Features:

Tax summary

Compliance calendar

Filing status

Notification alerts

Tax liability breakdown

This gives students a realistic view of how professionals manage compliance.

